{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_12","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /root/new-ralph-burning/.ralph/projects/ralph-burning-rewrite/loops/006-standard-preset-run-start-orchestration/20260311221639-spec.md\"","aggregated_output":"---\nartifact: spec\nloop: 6\nproject: ralph-burning-rewrite\nbackend: codex(gpt-5.4-xhigh)\nrole: planner\ncreated_at: 2026-03-11T22:16:39Z\n---\n\nI’m reviewing `prompt.md`, the completed loop specs, and recent git checkpoints to determine what is already built and what the next missing feature slice should be. After that I’ll map the current implementation against the roadmap and write the next spec in the required format.\nI’m gathering the project artifacts now: the master prompt, completed loop specs, and checkpoint history. Then I’ll verify the codebase aligns with those completed loops so I don’t re-plan something already present.\n`prompt.md` is not at the workspace root, so I’m locating the actual planning inputs and narrowing the inspection to the rewrite project and loop artifacts. After that I’ll read the completed specs and compare them to the current code paths.\nI’ve got the loop spec locations and confirmed the branch is currently at loop 5 complete. Next I’m reading the rewrite project’s own `prompt.md` plus the five approved specs and then checking the implementation surface for run orchestration gaps.\nThe codebase confirms loops 1 through 5: workspace init/config, flow registry, project/run record queries, stage contract validation/rendering, and the agent-execution facade are all present. I’m reading the approved specs directly now to pin the exact handoff boundary before choosing the next slice.\nThe likely handoff is roadmap step 6, but I’m verifying that nothing from `run start` orchestration or standard-flow persistence already landed outside the obvious CLI stub. I’m checking the loop-5 checkpoint diff and the current test inventory for any hidden vertical-path coverage.\nI’ve confirmed the missing surface is real: no `run start`, no run-orchestration service, and no conformance coverage for stage execution. I’m inspecting the existing storage and contract APIs now so the spec can target the exact integration seam instead of inventing a parallel design.\nI have the seam now: the project can validate contracts and invoke stub backends, but there is still no composition engine that moves a run through stages and persists the success path. I’m checking the existing shared domain types one last time so the spec names the right state objects and doesn’t duplicate what’s already there.\n# Feature: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration\n\n## Description\nLoops 1 through 5 are already complete in the approved specs and reflected in git checkpoints through the current loop-5 planning head: the rewrite has workspace/bootstrap commands, fixed flow presets, stage contracts and deterministic renderers, effective config plus active-project resolution, canonical project/run records and query commands, and the agent-execution facade with stub backend support. The next missing roadmap slice is step 6: implement the first real workflow engine behind `ralph-burning run start`.\n\nThis feature should add the straight-through `standard` preset execution path by wiring `workflow_composition`, `project_run_record`, and `agent_execution` together. It should execute enabled standard stages in canonical order, persist validated payloads and rendered artifacts at durable stage boundaries, and update `run.json` plus `journal.ndjson` as the source of truth. It should not yet add retry/remediation, resume, amendment-queue behavior, or non-standard flow execution.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ralph-burning run start` validates workspace version, active project selection, canonical project record integrity, and canonical run snapshot integrity before any mutation.\n- [ ] `run start` is allowed only when the project snapshot is `not_started` with no active run; running, paused, failed, or completed snapshots fail explicitly and never create a duplicate run.\n- [ ] This slice supports only projects with flow `standard`; `quick_dev`, `docs_change`, and `ci_improvement` fail with an explicit unsupported-for-now error and leave all canonical state unchanged.\n- [ ] The standard stage plan is derived from the existing flow definition in canonical order and honors `prompt_review.enabled`: when enabled, the run starts at `prompt_review`; when disabled, it starts at `planning` and writes no `prompt_review` history.\n- [ ] Before persisting `run_started`, the engine resolves stage-to-role/backend/model targets for every stage it will execute and performs capability plus availability preflight. If any preflight check fails, `run.json`, `journal.ndjson`, payloads, artifacts, sessions, and the active-project pointer remain unchanged.\n- [ ] On successful start, the engine creates exactly one new run ID and persists `run.json` with `status=running`, `active_run.stage_cursor` at the first executable stage, `cycle=1`, `attempt=1`, and `completion_round=1`, then appends `run_started` and first `stage_entered` journal events.\n- [ ] Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic and centralized: `prompt_review`/`planning` use `Planner`, `implementation` uses `Implementer`, `qa`/`acceptance_qa` use `QaValidator`, `review` uses `Reviewer`, and `completion_panel`/`final_review` use `CompletionJudge`.\n- [ ] Every stage invocation goes through `AgentExecutionService`; raw backend output is persisted only under `runtime/backend/`, and operational runtime logs are persisted only under `runtime/logs/`.\n- [ ] A stage is successful only after the validated payload JSON, rendered Markdown artifact, `stage_completed` journal event, and updated `run.json` / next-stage cursor are committed as one logical durable boundary. If payload write succeeds but artifact, journal, or snapshot persistence fails, the stage remains uncommitted: no paired history record is visible, no `stage_completed` event exists, and the cursor stays at the prior durable boundary.\n- [ ] On straight-through success with the stub backend, `run start` executes all enabled standard stages in order and ends with `run.json` status `completed`, `active_run=null`, `completion_rounds=1`, monotonic cycle/attempt values, and a terminal `run_completed` journal event persisted before any best-effort cleanup.\n- [ ] `run history` and `run tail` after a successful run show one payload/artifact pair per completed stage in canonical stage order and never include raw backend output or runtime logs unless `run tail --logs` is used.\n- [ ] This slice performs no retries. Any transport failure, schema-validation failure, domain-validation failure, timeout, cancellation, or non-passing QA/review outcome halts the run immediately and executes no later stages.\n- [ ] Failure invariants are explicit: if failure happens before `stage_entered`, that stage produces no journal or durable-history records; if failure happens after `stage_entered` but before successful commit, that stage may retain raw diagnostics only, but it has no payload/artifact pair, no `stage_completed`, and the run persists a failed state at that stage boundary.\n- [ ] Non-passing outcomes in `qa`, `review`, `completion_panel`, `acceptance_qa`, or `final_review` are terminal for this slice: the run is marked failed, no amendment-queue items are created, no completion round advances, and no remediation or resume logic is attempted.\n- [ ] Runtime-log append failures are cosmetic only: they must not fabricate, remove, or reorder durable history, and they must not turn an already committed stage into a failed durable-history state.\n- [ ] Add unit/service tests for stage-plan selection, preflight short-circuiting, happy-path completion, and atomic stage-commit failure handling.\n- [ ] Add CLI integration and Gherkin coverage for: successful standard `run start`, prompt-review-disabled start, active-run rejection, unsupported-flow rejection, preflight failure with no mutation, and mid-stage failure without partial durable-history exposure.\n- [ ] `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` pass.\n\n## Files to Modify/Create\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - implement `run start` and wire the orchestration dependencies while leaving `resume` and `rollback` for later slices\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs` - export the run engine and standard-stage-plan helpers\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` - add the standard-flow orchestration engine, stage-to-role mapping, preflight checks, and progression loop\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` - extend run and journal models for run lifecycle persistence and failed-stage summaries\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` - add mutation use cases for run start, stage commit, stage failure, and terminal completion\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` - add lifecycle event builders and sequence helpers for `run_started`, `stage_entered`, `stage_completed`, `run_completed`, and `run_failed`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - add run snapshot writes, atomic payload/artifact pair persistence, journal append sequencing, and runtime-log writing\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - add explicit orchestration and unsupported-flow errors for `run start`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs` - register new workflow-engine tests\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` - cover happy path, preflight short-circuiting, and failure invariants\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` - extend durable stage-commit and failed-run snapshot coverage\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/cli.rs` - add CLI integration coverage for `run start`\n- `ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature` - add public scenarios for standard `run start`\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires: Loops 2 through 5 (stage contracts/renderers, workspace governance, project/run record foundation, and agent execution facade)\n- Blocks: retry/remediation plus `run resume`, completion/acceptance/final-review amendment behavior, and non-standard flow execution support\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
